From: Johan Hovold <johan@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 20 Oct 2025 06:53:17 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] iommu/sun50i: fix device leak on of_xlate()
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.18.4
Git-commit: f916109bf53864605d10bf6f4215afa023a80406

commit f916109bf53864605d10bf6f4215afa023a80406 upstream.

Make sure to drop the reference taken to the iommu platform device when
looking up its driver data during of_xlate().

Fixes: 4100b8c229b3 ("iommu: Add Allwinner H6 IOMMU driver")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org	# 5.8
Cc: Maxime Ripard <mripard@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Robin Murphy <robin.murphy@arm.com>
Signed-off-by: Johan Hovold <johan@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Joerg Roedel <joerg.roedel@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/iommu/sun50i-iommu.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/iommu/sun50i-iommu.c b/drivers/iommu/sun50i-iommu.c
index de10b569d9a9..6306570d57db 100644
--- a/drivers/iommu/sun50i-iommu.c
+++ b/drivers/iommu/sun50i-iommu.c
@@ -839,6 +839,8 @@ static int sun50i_iommu_of_xlate(struct device *dev,
 
 	dev_iommu_priv_set(dev, platform_get_drvdata(iommu_pdev));
 
+	put_device(&iommu_pdev->dev);
+
 	return iommu_fwspec_add_ids(dev, &id, 1);
 }
 
